<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{five}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs form the passive by taking the @HI{{nai}} stem and adding the
suffix @HI{{reru}}.
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{ichi}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs form the passive by dropping the final @HI{{ru}} and adding the
suffix @HI{{rareru}}. This means that the
<a href="grammar-verb-formation-potential.html"> potential </a> form and
passive form of @KJ{{ichi}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs
are identical and must be distinguished based on context.
</p>

<p>
The two irregular verbs conjugate as shown above.
</p>

<p>
All passive verbs conjugate into further forms as @KJ{{ichi}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs.
</p>

